---
const highlights = [
  { label: 'Location', value: 'Bogotá, Colombia — open to remote, hybrid or on-site' },
  { label: 'Languages', value: 'Spanish (native) · English C1 · French B1' },
  { label: 'Degree', value: 'Systems Engineering, Universidad ean (6th semester)' },
  { label: 'Certification', value: 'AWS Certified Cloud Practitioner' },
];
---

<section id="about" class="py-20 border-t border-neutral-800 scroll-mt-20">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">

    <p class="text-xs text-neutral-500 uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">About</p>
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-100 mb-12">The path that brought me here</h2>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-12">

      <div class="lg:col-span-2 space-y-5 text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          My path into software engineering started somewhere unexpected. Before code, I built a
          technical foundation through a degree in Occupational Safety and Health Administration —
          work that required structured thinking, attention to systems, and a methodical approach to
          complex problems. In 2018, I decided to invest in my future and moved to Melbourne,
          Australia for two years, studying at Greenwich College and Focus Language School. That
          experience went beyond language — it shaped how I communicate, think internationally, and
          work under pressure.
        </p>
        <p>
          When I returned to Colombia, I committed fully to software. Through the Misión TIC program
          at Universidad Tecnológica de Pereira in 2022, I built my first solid foundation in
          full-stack development. That same year I joined UColtis as a Full Stack Developer,
          contributing to EdTech applications built on Java 11, Spring Boot, Python, Django and Flask
          — integrating backend services with REST APIs and working across MySQL and MongoDB
          databases. I enrolled in Systems Engineering at Universidad ean shortly after, and I've
          been combining formal study with professional work ever since.
        </p>
        <p>
          From early 2024 to early 2025, I worked as a Backend Developer at J Create, a
          Tokyo-based company working across metal manufacturing, architectural products and
          construction solutions, fully remote. There I focused on database optimization, backend
          architecture, and building a custom CRM that streamlined internal workflows for sales and
          support teams. Today I'm in my 6th semester, cloud-certified on both AWS and Google Cloud,
          and focused on building reliable backend systems — APIs, microservices, and cloud
          infrastructure. I'm looking for opportunities where I can contribute real technical work
          and grow within a team with clear engineering standards.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p class="text-xs text-neutral-500 uppercase tracking-widest mb-4">Details</p>
        <ul class="space-y-4">
          {highlights.map(({ label, value }) => (
            <li>
              <p class="text-xs text-neutral-600 mb-0.5">{label}</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-neutral-300">{value}</p>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>
